### `man_1_simple_shell`

```roff
.TH hsh 1 "April 2025" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [scriptfile]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX shell program written in C. It reads commands from standard input or a script file and executes them.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
Interactive mode:
Displays a prompt and waits for the user to type a command.
.TP
Non-interactive mode:
Reads commands from a script or piped input and executes them.

.SH USAGE
.TP
To start the shell:
.B ./hsh

.TP
To run in non-interactive mode:
.B echo "ls" | ./hsh

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.

.SH AUTHORS
